<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd20bda55-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s3959"><num value="3959">§ 3959.</num><heading> Extension of protections to dependents</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Upon application to a court, a dependent of a servicemember is entitled to the protections of this subchapter if the dependent’s ability to comply with a lease, contract, bailment, or other obligation is materially affected by reason of the servicemember’s military service.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd20bda56-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1940-10-17/ch888">Oct. 17, 1940, ch. 888</ref>, title III, § 308, as added <ref href="/us/pl/108/189/s1">Pub. L. 108–189, § 1</ref>, <date date="2003-12-19">Dec. 19, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/2851">117 Stat. 2851</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd20bda57-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd20bda58-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd20bda59-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to section 538 of the former Appendix to this title prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idd20bda5a-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idd20bda5b-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section applicable to any case not final before <date date="2003-12-19">Dec. 19, 2003</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/108/189/s3">section 3 of Pub. L. 108–189</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t50/s3901">section 3901 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
